Panjiva is a supply chain analytics platform, covering 8 million companies and an over 1 billion shipment records. Data is sourced from 18 countries; it is the largest dataset of its kind. The platform allows users to track shipments, volumes, supplier, and buyers, with 
search capabilities by product name or classification, commodity name, HS / HTS code, D-U-N-SÂ® Number, and location-based searches. Research and case studies, along with educational videos, are available on the platform. 
Access information
For Hackathon participants, go to panjiva.com  and log in as follows:
Username: covid19hackathon@panjiva.com, Password: Panjiva2020
Users will be unable to get the kind of download that gets emailed to them, but can ask for it via the Slack channel.
